CI Looks at U.S. After Scotiabank ‘Lost Interest,’ Globe Says

-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 
2011-02-24T12:24:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/ci-looks-at-u-s-after-scotiabank-lost-interest-globe-says.html
  CI Financial Corp . is looking to the
U.S. for acquisitions after minority shareholder  Bank of Nova
Scotia  indicated it’s not interested in raising its stake in the
Canadian mutual fund company, the Globe and Mail reported,
citing Chief Executive Officer Stephen MacPhail.  CI was told in December that Bank of Nova Scotia wasn’t
interested in buying the 62 percent of the Toronto-based fund
manager it doesn’t already own, the  newspaper  said. Bank of Nova
Scotia agreed in November to buy DundeeWealth Corp.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sean B. Pasternak in Toronto at 
 spasternak@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scanlan at 
 dscanlan@bloomberg.net  